/#
   A type that is different from AdjustableDate in two regards. First, date adjustments can be specified with either a dateAdjustments element or a reference to an existing dateAdjustments element. Second, it does not require the specification of date adjustments.
 #/
record FpML5.reporting.AdjustableDate2 {
  # A date subject to adjustment.
  unadjustedDate : date?

  # The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business dat in the specified business centers.
  dateAdjustments : FpML5.reporting.BusinessDayAdjustments

  # A pointer style reference to date adjustments defined elsewhere in the document.
  dateAdjustmentsReference : FpML5.reporting.BusinessDayAdjustmentsReference

  # The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
  adjustedDate : date?

  id : string?

}

dateAdjustments.Doc: The business day convention and financial business centers used for adjusting the date if it would otherwise fall on a day that is not a business dat in the specified business centers.
dateAdjustments.Name: dateAdjustments

dateAdjustmentsReference.Doc: A pointer style reference to date adjustments defined elsewhere in the document.
dateAdjustmentsReference.Name: dateAdjustmentsReference

adjustedDate.Doc: The date once the adjustment has been performed. (Note that this date may change if the business center holidays change).
adjustedDate.Name: adjustedDate
